{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund pay rises for teachers in line with inflation",
        "additional_details": "Everyone is entitled to an education as it equips them for later life. Teaching is hard work and the pay does not reflect that. As a consequence, there is a shortage of teachers. Politicians should respect teachers by paying them a fair wage.",
        "background": "We believe that teachers should be paid fairly. As inflation rises, teachers' pay haven't increased at the same rate. Instead of increasing at 2-3% for the next two years, we believe it should be raised in line with inflation, and by 9.1% this year (matching the current inflation rate).",
